
[1]synodical

   SYNOD'ICAL, a. Pertaining to a synod; transacted in a synod; as
   synodical proceedings or forms; a synodical epistle.

   Synodical month, in astronomy, is the period from one conjunction of
   the moon with the sun to another. This is called also a lunation,
   because in the course of it the moon exhibits all its phases. This
   month consists of 29 days, 12 hours, 44 minutes, 3 seconds and 11
   thirds.
